Skye Bank of Nigeria to Raise 50 Billion Naira, Punch Reports

-- B y   V i n c e n t   N w a n m a
-- 
2011-05-24T09:24:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-24/skye-bank-of-nigeria-to-raise-50-billion-naira-punch-reports.html
Skye Bank Plc (SKYEBANK) , a Nigerian lender,
plans to raise 50 billion naira ($319 million) of capital
through a debt sale, Punch  reported , citing Kehinde Durosinmi-
Etti, the managing director.  The amount will be raised through a public offering or a
placement with selected investors, the Lagos-based newspaper
said. Skye Bank will use the funds to increase its share in oil
and gas exploration and production, telecommunication,
agriculture, power and infrastructure development, the newspaper
reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Vincent Nwanma in Lagos at 
 vnwanma@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 